content: Precisely what I was looking for. Straightforward tracking of kcals, and separate nutrient sources, e.g. protein and fat. Plenty of standard food sources already filled in and useful calory estimates depending on age/weight/sex to lose weight or build muscle.

This is a nice app with lots of features, but there is at least one major stumble and a lesser one. All food is input as ounces, but this makes it very hard to input food easily and quickly. The users is left to do all the math conversions. The app should have a drop down menu with grams, ounces, tablespoon, teaspoon, cups, etc. The minor issue is there are far too few icons to choose from in the app. Still purchased, but looking forward updates.
Great app, I never give 5 stars unless that app does something no other app has ever done before. Great at helping you track you intake and program in restaurants calories.

Really good. I lost 15 kilos pain-free. I just put in how much I wanted to lose per week, how much exercize I could commit to, and it did the rest. It really calms you down and takes the angst out of trying to lose weight. Try it!

App has a glaring bug lately. Almost every dang time I go to enter a new snack/meal, when I choose the weight of the food and add it to my "wave," the food type changes to the previous food I entered. For example, if I added 1oz of butter at 10am, then returned at noon to say I ate an apple that was 4oz, the app creates a second entry of butter; rather than the apple, and I end up logging way more calories than I've actually eaten. Then I have to delete the second helping of butter, and search for apples again, and re-enter those calories. It's EXTREMELY frustrating. Happens multiple times a day.

This is a great app.  This is why.  I'd been using the free app for quite a while and it had really helped in my weight loss. At this point I've lost 20.4 kg in weight!  It's not only because of this app, but the app has played a big part.  I like the calorie graph and the calorie counter parts.  They are what i use, the exercise part is wasted on me as all I do is just walk the üêï's legs off. Two pieces of advice about this app.  Spend a while inputting your favourites and your custom foods and snacks then it becomes very quick and easy to add your food to the count.  Weigh yourself on the same day at the same time every week and input the info on the graph.  It becomes amazingly encouraging (my best was 2.6kg down in a week - yup i know its not recommended but...anyway usually it's been around 1 to 2kg a week).  So ive been happy with the free app and figured that he deserved the money for the paid app (I mean what would you pay someone if they helped you get rid of 20.4kg (and counting).  There are some tweaks I'd make the app if i were the developer - more brighter colour choices, custom photo uploads for backgrounds, user choice of elements on homepage.  But.  It works as it is.  So i bought it to say thank you.

Great graphics, encourages and charts progress well. Calorie guides not comprehensive, but very easy to add your own. Visual displays for fat, protein and carbs each day v good, and you have a real sense of how much you should eat in what's left of the day because it is so clear.
Geat App. I very much like that it also calculates the fat, carb and protein intake. Thanks a lot.
This is a fabulous app.  Everything I need is there.

This application needs improvments , it does not contain any ready famous meals or beverages in the data base , so if I have a starbucks coffee I have to add all the drink ingredients separetly , I can not keep favourites like my everyday breakfast , Launch ... , the reminders did not work with me , I did not find it easy to use.
Perfect app to lose weight

I like most of the features. Nice style, nice widget for glancing at how many calories are left. Wish there were a few more lighter color choices, I find that more soothing. Also, would really like the total calories displayed on the add window just BEFORE it's added to the daily total, so I can gauge how accurate the amount is. It's irritating to not know, and then once added realize that's not the right amount and go back and edit it. Also calories chart should be dots, not blocks. The charts could be a little better design. Love, being able to add my own frequent foods, and having basic food calories handy! Thanks!
This is a great app for tracking your fitness progress. It has a lot of tools to monitor your fitness activities and nutrition level.
Works for me.
I love it but I wish that also it has the other drinks in the known shops like Starbucks' the iced and the phraps for example and to have more salads like salmon salad.. Thank you
Solid well rounded app
Good stuff
Love this app. I was struggling to find a simple way to track my food and I have! Thanks!
I keep coming back to this app.
This is an awesome and easy app to use. I don't have a lot of time to waste so I tried a bunch of others and this is the best by far. Keep up the great work.
